  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Multi-Sectoral Humanitarian Emergency Response to Save Lives and Protect Returnees in Hodh Ech Chargui</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">According to the latest reports and analyses from the various UN agencies, the situation of insecurity in Mauritania, marked by violent attacks at the beginning of the year, should persist. Due to insecurity in Mali, 7,827 Malians (2,412 households) and 5,570 Mauritanian returnees (1,114 households) have arrived in Mauritania since January 2022. The return of Mauritanians accompanied by a herd of nearly 800,000 heads, places an additional strain on already limited resources and requires an urgent response from the authorities and humanitarian partners. This project allows IOM to provide emergency humanitarian assistance to the most vulnerable Mauritanian returnees in the Hodh Ech Chargui region. Based on IOM&apos;s assessment through its Emergency Tracking Tool (ETT), IOM&apos;s response focuses on accessibility to drinking water for humans and animals, urgent distribution of animal feed and emergency vaccination to strengthen the livelihoods of returned; and providing households with non-food items.</narrative>
  </description>
